  1876                                  ;
  1877                                  ;       IRQ1    Keyboard Interrupt
  1878                                  ;
  1879                                  ;       This handler is called when an IRQ1 hardware interrupt occurs, caused by a keyboard event. The scan-code(s)
  1880                                  ;       corresponding to the keyboard event are read and message events are appended to the message queue. Since this
  1881                                  ;       code is called in response to a hardware interrupt, no task switch occurs. We need to preseve the state of
  1882                                  ;       ALL modified registers upon return.
